    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`vim.on_key` callback can listen to \"secret\" input:\n\n- `vim.fn.inputsecret`\n- `vim.ui.input` ([ref](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37549))\n- `sudo` in `:terminal`\n\nAlthough plugins generally must be assumed to be \"trusted\" (since they can already run arbitrary commands via `system()` or [monkey patch core functions](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37549#issuecomment-4369326122)), it's likely unexpected and may lead to accidental \"leaks\" of user secrets if, for example, a plugin unintentionally logs a password somewhere.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`vim.on_key` should be skipped for the above scenarios.\n\nIn `:terminal`, it may be possible to detect when `sudo` is used. For example, this UI shows how ghostty handles it:\n\n<img width=\"497\" height=\"158\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6228676d-6225-403d-8623-82742c26537b\" />",
